Firefighters are battling a fire which has broken out at Pearly Beach near Gaansbaai in the Overberg District of the Western Cape. No damage to property or injuries has been reported at this stage. Homeowners have been informed of the fire. Overberg Municipality Fire Chief Reinhard Geldenhuys says they hope to contain the fire by Tuesday evening. “The fire at Pearly Beach, we managed to bring it fairly under control. We have four fire trucks, 20 ground crew from Working on Fire and the Working on Fire helicopter working the lines,” says Geldenhuys.